<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Choose a sample application</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  We've prepared 3 realistic planning applications. Choose any one to test with:
</p>

<div class="ndx-sample-documents-grid">
  {% for doc in planningSampleDocuments %}
    <div class="ndx-sample-document-card">
      <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">{{ doc.title }}</h4>

      <dl class="govuk-summary-list govuk-summary-list--no-border">
        <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
          <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">Type</dt>
          <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">{{ doc.type }}</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
          <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">Applicant</dt>
          <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">{{ doc.applicant }}</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
          <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">Address</dt>
          <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">{{ doc.address }}</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
          <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">Description</dt>
          <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">{{ doc.description }}</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
          <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">File size</dt>
          <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">{{ doc.fileSize }}</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>

      <div class="ndx-document-download govuk-!-margin-top-3">
        <a href="{{ doc.documentUrl }}" download class="govuk-button govuk-button--secondary" data-module="govuk-button">
          Download PDF
        </a>
        <p class="govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-top-2" style="color: #505a5f;">
          Processing time: {{ doc.timeToProcess }}
        </p>
      </div>

      {# Preview what will be extracted #}
      <details class="govuk-details govuk-!-margin-top-3">
        <summary class="govuk-details__summary">
          <span class="govuk-details__summary-text">
            What AI will extract from this document
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="govuk-details__text">
          <p class="govuk-body-s">The AI extraction will identify these {{ doc.fields.length }} fields:</p>
          <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet govuk-body-s">
            {% for field in doc.fields %}
              <li><strong>{{ field.name }}:</strong> {{ field.extracted }}</li>
            {% endfor %}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  {% endfor %}
</div>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Download instructions</h3>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Pick one sample document</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      We recommend starting with "House Extension Application" - it's the quickest to process.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Click "Download PDF"</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      The PDF will download to your default downloads folder
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Note the file location</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      You'll need to find this file in the next step to upload it. Most browsers show
      downloads in the bottom-left corner or in a downloads bar.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Optional: Preview the PDF</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Open the PDF to see what a realistic planning application looks like. Notice where
      the applicant name, address, and description appear in the document.
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>

<div class="govuk-inset-text">
  <p class="govuk-body">
    <strong>Tip:</strong> If you want to test multiple documents, you can come back to this step
    later and try a different application type.
  </p>
</div>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Understanding the sample documents</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Each sample document represents a common planning application type:
</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>
    <strong>House Extension Application (Householder):</strong> Most common type - small extensions
    to existing dwellings. Typically 2-4 page applications.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Change of Use Application (Full):</strong> More complex - changing building purpose.
    Includes multiple use classes and floor area calculations.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>New Dwelling Application (Outline):</strong> Most detailed - new building proposals.
    Includes site area, dwelling counts, and detailed descriptions.
  </li>
</ul>

<div class="govuk-warning-text govuk-!-margin-top-4">
  <span class="govuk-warning-text__icon" aria-hidden="true">!</span>
  <strong class="govuk-warning-text__text">
    <span class="govuk-visually-hidden">Note</span>
    These are realistic sample documents with fictional applicant details. They follow
    standard UK planning application formats but contain no real personal information.
  </strong>
</div>

{# AC-3.3.7: Troubleshooting #}
<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Troubleshooting</h3>

<details class="govuk-details">
  <summary class="govuk-details__summary">
    <span class="govuk-details__summary-text">
      Download link not working
    </span>
  </summary>
  <div class="govuk-details__text">
    <p class="govuk-body">
      If clicking "Download PDF" doesn't work:
    </p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>Right-click the button and choose "Save link as..."</li>
      <li>Check your browser's download settings aren't blocking PDFs</li>
      <li>Try a different browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge all supported)</li>
      <li>Check you have enough disk space for the file (1-4 MB)</li>
      <li>Disable browser extensions that might block downloads</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</details>

<details class="govuk-details">
  <summary class="govuk-details__summary">
    <span class="govuk-details__summary-text">
      Can't find downloaded file
    </span>
  </summary>
  <div class="govuk-details__text">
    <p class="govuk-body">
      If you can't locate the downloaded PDF:
    </p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>Check your browser's Downloads page (usually Ctrl+J or Cmd+Shift+J)</li>
      <li>Look in your default Downloads folder</li>
      <li>Search your computer for "sample-house-extension.pdf" (or the document name)</li>
      <li>Check if your browser asks where to save files - you may have saved it elsewhere</li>
      <li>Try downloading again and watch where your browser saves it</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</details>

<details class="govuk-details">
  <summary class="govuk-details__summary">
    <span class="govuk-details__summary-text">
      PDF won't open or looks corrupted
    </span>
  </summary>
  <div class="govuk-details__text">
    <p class="govuk-body">
      If the PDF won't open or displays incorrectly:
    </p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>Try opening with Adobe Reader or another PDF viewer</li>
      <li>Re-download the file - the download may have been interrupted</li>
      <li>Check the file size matches what's shown (1.2 MB, 2.8 MB, or 3.5 MB)</li>
      <li>Ensure you have a PDF reader installed on your computer</li>
      <li>Try a different sample document</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</details>

